parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, stalling, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's oil level low light comes on frequently
requiring frequent oil top-offs
and the engine may stall or struggle to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, and potentially cause accidents or fires.
symptoms: The coolant level is low
the coolant pump and thermostat housing are leaking
and the vehicle may overheat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain and tensioner failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The engine may vibrate or stall
and the timing chain may stretch or break
causing damage to the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes very difficult to turn
the steering wheel seizes
the steering system malfunction warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle veers to one side while driving
the steering wheel has a notchy or stiff feeling
the vehicle is unable to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electromechanical steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel has a notchy or stiff feeling
the vehicle drifts to one side while driving
the steering wheel jerks to center uncontrolled
the vehicle is difficult to keep straight
the steering wheel has a whistling sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack module can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes very difficult to turn
the steering wheel seizes
the steering system malfunction warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle is unable to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or even fires, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Coolant pump becomes blocked
engine overheating
smoke or fire coming from under the hood
repeated blowing of fuses
loud squealing or grinding noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries, and can also result in engine stalling or failure.
symptoms: Smoke or fire coming from under the hood
repeated blowing of fuses
loud squealing or grinding noises from the engine
warning lights flashing on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the adaptive lighting system can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Adaptive light not functioning
warning light flashing on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the audio system can cause sudden loud noises, which can be startling and distracting, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Loud popping or cracking noises from the speakers
even when the volume is turned down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to complete recall work can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealership charging for recall work
recall work not completed.
